National Super Alliance (NASA) presidential nominee Raila Odinga has been formally endorsed by ODM delegates to be the party&rsquo;s flag bearer in the forthcoming General Election. ODM National Delegates Convention at Kasarani Stadium unanimously sanctioned Raila Odinga&rsquo;s candidature. NASA principals, Wiper leader Kalonzo Musyoka and ANC leader Musalia Mudavadi were present during the occasion. The Deputy party leader of ODM Hassan Ali Joho urged Coast residents to vote for Raila Odinga for he has spearheaded development in the region. He recommended Raila&rsquo;s presidency that will kick out poverty in Kenya and enhance standards of living among the citizens. ALSO READ: Thousands converge at Kasarani to endorse Raila for presidential race Raila now clinches the ODM presidential ticket to battle it out with Jubilee&rsquo;s Uhuru Kenyatta in August polls. &nbsp;